OL,3,CFarmer says ME 'stole his childhood'
OL,4,Cwhile living in the Isle of Man
OL,6,F"Some days, I didn't have the energy
OL,7,Fto brush my teeth myself. Which for a
OL,8,Fvery active farm boy was incredibly
OL,9,Fdifficult."
OL,11,FAs a result of the ME, Thomase says
OL,12,Fhis aspirations to leave the island
OL,13,Fand travel around the world have been
OL,14,Fseverely limited.
OL,16,FHe said: "I wanted to be an
OL,17,Fagricultural consultant, I wanted to
OL,18,Ftravel the world, and even to this day
OL,19,Fit's unrealistic to move away from
OL,20,Fhome and work on my own without a
OL,21,Fsupport system there."
