OL,6,FWhile on the Isle of Man, his finds
OL,7,Fsupport in the company of his animals
OL,8,Fon the farm.
OL,10,F"They give you something to get up for
OL,11,Fin the morning and I very much think
OL,12,Fthey can sense when I'm on a low
OL,13,Fbecause I'm not as 'with them', I'm
OL,14,Fmuch more 'out of it'.
OL,16,F"They mean the world to me, I couldn't
OL,17,Fbe without them", he concluded.
